@page "/websites"

<header>
	<div class="modal-header slide-in-from-bottom">
		<h1>Websites</h1>
	</div>

</header>
<body>
	<div>
		<div class="row slide-in-from-bottom-light">
            <div class="column to-slide-bottom-light animate">
                <div class="card" onclick="document.getElementById('id02').style.display='block'">
                    <div class="img-container">
                        <img src="/Images/portfoliov2.png" alt="Potfolio version 2 Logo">
                    </div>
                    <div class="container">
                        <h4><b>Portfolio.v2</b></h4>
                        <p>Full Stack Django Developer</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
			<div class="column to-slide-bottom-light animate">
				<div class="card" onclick="document.getElementById('id01').style.display='block'">
					<div class="img-container">
						<img src="/Images/voting_system.png" alt="Voting System Logo">
					</div>
					<div class="container">
						<h4><b>Voting System</b></h4>
						<p>Front End Developer</p>
					</div>
				</div>
			</div>
			<div class="column to-slide-bottom-light animate">
			</div>
		</div>
		<br />
	</div>
</body>

<!-- The Modal -->
<div id="id01" class="modal" onclick="document.getElementById('id01').style.display='none'">
	<span onclick="document.getElementById('id01').style.display='none'"
		  class="close" title="Close Modal">&times;</span>

	<!-- Modal Content -->
	<form class="modal-content animate">
        <div class="fappy_container">
            <h1 class="text-center">Voting System</h1>
            <hr />
            <br />
            <div class="text-center">
                <img src="/Images/voting_system.png" alt="Voting System Logo">
            </div>
            <br /><br />
            <p>
                <b>What it is</b><br />
                Voting System is a website Kalen created for his software engineering (CSCE 361) final project at the University of Nebraska-Lincoln.
                <br />
                <br />
                <b>Features</b><br />
                The main feature of the Voting System is the ability to vote. The website also handles user accounts, allows the user
                to view their ballot after voting, and view the results of an election.
                <br />
                <br />
                <b>Team & Responsibilities</b><br />
                Kalen's team consisted of 5 student software engineers. He developed all of the front end and unit tested the controllers.
                Josh Bellmyer created the controllers and methods for using the database and handling user information.
                Thomas Walton and Jayden Carlon designed and implemented the database.
                Cameron Collingham helped Josh with some of the controllers and helped Kalen write unit tests.
                <br />
                <br />
                <b>Development Details</b><br />
                The project was developed using <b>MVC</b> and <b>SOLID</b> design principles.
                <br />
                <a class="font-weight-bold">Development Tools:</a> .NET Framework, ASP.NET Core 3.1, Razor Pages
                <br />
                <a class="font-weight-bold">Languages:</a> HTML, CSS, C#, and Javascript.
                <br />
                <a class="font-weight-bold">Testing Framework:</a> MSTest
                <br />
                <a class="font-weight-bold">Database:</a> Entity Framework Core, Uses LINQ to query data, prevent attacks, SQL Server/Local DB
            </p>
            <button class="btn-block" type="button" onclick="document.getElementById('id01').style.display='none'">Done</button>
        </div>
	</form>
</div>

<!-- The Modal -->
<div id="id02" class="modal" onclick="document.getElementById('id02').style.display='none'">
	<span onclick="document.getElementById('id02').style.display='none'"
		  class="close" title="Close Modal">&times;</span>

	<!-- Modal Content -->
	<form class="modal-content animate">
		<div class="fappy_container">
			<h1 class="text-center">Portfolio.v2</h1>
			<hr />
			<br />
            <iframe loading="lazy" frameborder="0" src="https://dj.kalenwallin.com/" allowfullscreen="" width="980" height="688"></iframe>
			<br /><br />
			<p>
				<b>What it is</b><br />
				Portfolio.v2 is a new portfolio website currently in progress. This site showcases Kalen's growth as a web developer and is a playground for him to test new ideas.
				It contains the same content as here, so no need to reread everything! The design was inspired by Netflix.
				<br />
				<br />
				<b>Features</b><br />
				Like posts to show support.
				<br />
				<br />
				<a class="font-weight-bold">Development Tools:</a> Django, PythonAnywhere
				<br />
				<a class="font-weight-bold">Languages:</a> HTML, CSS, Javascript, and Python
			</p>
			<button class="btn-block" type="button" onclick="document.getElementById('id02').style.display='none'">Done</button>
		</div>
	</form>
</div>